					<h3 >9. Eat Less Meat </h3>
					<img src="img/way9_1.jpg" class="img-responsive pull-left img-margin" alt="way9">
					<p >Buy organic and locally grown foods. Avoid processed items. Grow some of your own food. And eat low on the food chain — at least one meat-free meal a day — since 18 per cent of greenhouse gas emissions come from meat and dairy production. Food writer Michael Pollan sums it up best: "Eat food. Not too much. Mostly plants."</p>
